ring, and cross-functional partners. The ideal candidate will be data oriented, and have experience managing technical programs. What You'll Be Doing (i.e., Job Duties) Be the point person & first responder for all things Bootcamp-related Drive strategic high-level initiatives to build and enhance our suite of programs, both independently and by managing contributions of stakeholders Recruit, onboard, train and manage mentors, pulled from our most senior engineering population Partner closely with Engineering to develop program specific content & train presenters Improve processes and put processes in place where none exist Measure the impact of bootcamp, and use data to propose programmatic improvements and drive implementation Run all weekly meetings & drive forward progress Work with recruiting and engineering managers to ensure seamless placement of new hires on teams Lead all communications with key stakeholders across the org Maintain and streamline operational logistics Work with coordinator to lead and measure success of all networking events Manage and iterate program to meet company level priorities Take on additional Technical learning projects/programs as needed What We Look For In You (ie. Job Requirements) Bachelor\u2019s Degree and 5-10 years experience in corporate or technical learning, technical onboarding or complex program/project management Proven ability to manage multiple projects and meet deadlines Ability to build relationships and drive alignment with excellent verbal and written communication skills Highly motivated and hard-working with ability to think clearly under pressure, both individually and in-team environment Detail oriented and organized Data driven Benefits at Coinbase Health, Dental, and Vision insurance covered at 100% for employees and 80% for dependents HSA plan with company seed Disability and Life Insurance 401(k) plan with company match $260 monthly Commuter Benefit Monthly Gym Benefit Volunteer Time Off Fertility Counse